To see Node list-----> kubectl get nodes
To see pod list -----> kubectl get pods
To create pod ------>  kubectl apply -f <pod_filename.yaml>
To see on which worker node pod has created ------>kubectl describe pod <pod_Name>
To see logs of pod ----> kubectl log <pod_name>
To see details of pod ----> kubectl get pods -o wide
To see service list ---> kubectl get svc
To create svc ----> kubectl apply -f <service_filename.yml>
To delete all the resource  ----> kubectl delete all --all
To delete pod ----> kubectl delete pod <PodName>
To get Namespace list ---> kubectl get namespace
To see a pods that are running under which namespace ----> kubectl get pods -n <NameSpaceName>
Create custom namespace in k8s cluster ---> kubectl create ns <NameSpaceName>
To delete Namespace -----> kubectl delete ns <NameSpaceName>
To get ReplicationController details ----> kubectl get rc
To scale up and scale down ReplicationController ----> kubectl scale rc <RCName> --replicas 3
To Check Rollout Status(new version) ----> kubectl rollout status deployment/<deployment-name> -n <namespace>
To Check Rollout History ----> kubectl rollout history deployment/<deployment-name> -n <namespace>
To Rollback to Previous Version(undo) ----> kubectl rollout undo deployment/<deployment-name> -n <namespace>
To Verify the New Image Version ----> kubectl describe pod <new-pod-name> -n vk67220-ns | grep Image
To see cluster detail ---> aws eks describe-cluster --name eks-practice --region us-east-1
To see ConfigMap details ---> kubectl get configmap -n vk67220-ns
To see Secret details ---> kubectl get secret -n vk67220-ns
To verify ConfigMap info ---> kubectl describe configmap -n vk67220-ns
To verify secret info ---> kubectl describe secret -n vk67220-ns
echo -n postgres|base64
echo -n root|base64
To see StorageClasses details ---> kubectl get storageclass -n vk67220-ns
To verify StorageClasses info ---> kubectl describe storageclass -n vk67220-ns
To see PVC details ---> kubectl get pvc -n vk67220-ns
To verify PVC info ---> kubectl describe pvc -n vk67220-ns
To delete StorageClass ---> kubectl delete storageclass <storageclass_name>
To delete pvc ---> kubectl delete pvc <pvc_name> -n vk67220-ns
To Delete Statefulset --> kubectl delete statefulset <statefulset_name> -n namespace




